#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:116
msgid ""
"The presence of Master Perrin's journeymen gives you the ability to recruit "
"mages."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:126
msgid ""
"We should be on the outskirts of the settled country around Kal Kartha, but "
"something doesn't feel right here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:130
msgid "It's too quiet...and I think I smell traces of smoke on the wind."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ratheln
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:134
msgid ""
"I do not sense hostile magic in the vicinity. But there has been fire near "
"here recently, and not a clean one."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:138
msgid ""
"Look sharp for the inhabitants here. They might have something to tell us."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:145
msgid "Find the inhabitants"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Peasant
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:184
msgid "Ollin"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ollin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:192
msgid "Don't kill me, masters! Please don't kill me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:196
msgid "You're in no danger from us. What lies to the east of here?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ollin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:200
msgid "You wear no mask. You...you're not with them?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:204
msgid "What are you talking about?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ollin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:208
msgid "The masked dwarves. Killing, burning, kidnapping. Look..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Masked Dwarf Leader
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:229
msgid ""
"Fellow dwarves, hail! We're looking for a human refugee, one named Ollin. "
"Have you seen him? Our master demands his life."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:233
msgid "He is here. How has he wronged your master, that you seek his death?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Masked Dwarf Leader
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:237
msgid ""
"Does it matter? He is only a dirtgrubbing human, not fit to polish the boots "
"of the true people."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:241
msgid ""
"What is your name, masked one? Will you stand behind your deed? I am a "
"witness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Masked Dwarf Leader
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:245
msgid ""
"A witness? My name is...my name is not important. My deed will speak its own "
"truth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:249
msgid ""
"You speak without honor. Mine is the power of our ancient Law; speak your "
"name and give up your murder, or the Law will cast you forth. I am a witness!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Masked Dwarf Leader
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:253
msgid ""
"If you were a witness of the true people, you would not let a dirtgrubber "
"hide behind your robes. I deny you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:257
msgid "Up axes!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:261
msgid "The Law speaks: you are cast out. You are un-dwarf. I AM A WITNESS!"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:268
msgid "Defeat the Masked Dwarf"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ollin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:294
msgid "Take that for my family's memory, you murderer!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:302
msgid "They are defeated"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:306
msgid "You have acted in honor. I am a witness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:310
msgid ""
"I have never seen the formal banishment before. One reads of it in the old "
"tales, of course, but to hear it with one's own ears? It was...unsettling."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:314
msgid ""
"It is not something we do often. The last such was in my grandsire's time. "
"But look at what these filth were carrying if you have any doubt it was "
"merited."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:318
msgid ""
"Whips. Shackles. No, Angarthing, I would not doubt you, even if it were my "
"place to doubt a loremaster."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:322
msgid ""
"They were seeking captives. To what purpose, I cannot say. But I doubt it "
"was any good one."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:3
msgid "Forbidden Forest"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Elvish High Lord
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:46
msgid "Telcherion"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Elvish High Lord
#. [side]: type=Elvish Lady
#. [side]: type=Ancient Wose
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:61
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:83
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:107
msgid "Forest"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Elvish Lady
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:69
msgid "Iluvarda"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Ancient Wose
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:91
msgid "Burumardir-Athelorand"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Elvish Scout
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:148
msgid "Elurin"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elurin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:157
msgid "Who disturbs our forest?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:162
msgid ""
"A delegation of the Northern Alliance, seeking the road through to Kal "
"Kartha."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elurin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:167
msgid ""
"We allow few outsiders in our forest paths, and no dwarves since the masked "
"ones began to trouble our eastern margins. No axe-bearers shall come near "
"our trees. Return whence you came!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:172
msgid "No. We have our duty. We must pass."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elurin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:177
msgid "You shall not pass here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:182
msgid ""
"Winter comes on our heels, and your forest straddles the only gap in these "
"mountains. You leave us no choice but to fight you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elurin
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:187
msgid ""
"So be it, then. Yours will not be the first bones to nourish the earth of "
"our forest."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:208
msgid "Move both Aiglondur and Angarthing to the eastern signpost"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:236
msgid ""
"Rally on me, everyone. We have better things to do than brawl with elves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/09_Forbidden_Forest.cfg:268
msgid "Kal Kartha should be only another day's march east of here."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:3
msgid "The Siege of Kal Kartha"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Dwarvish Steelclad
#. [side]: type=Dwarvish Steelclad
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:100
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:39
msgid "Dulcatulos"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Orcish Warlord
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:64
msgid "Tan-Morgh"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Orcish Warlord
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:107
msgid "Tan-Garukh"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Orcish Warlord
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:140
msgid "Tan-Wagran"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:196
msgid "Behold! The West Gate of Kal Kartha!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:200
msgid ""
"And under siege, I see. There is a mighty host of orcs between us and that "
"gate."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tan-Morgh
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:204
msgid ""
"Ahhh...more stinky-midgets, come to get killed just like these cowards in "
"their den."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:208
msgid "Let us bring our kin that orc's head as a guesting-gift."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:227
msgid "Death of West Gate commander"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:245
msgid "Kal Kartha is taken. Our mission has failed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:258
msgid ""
"Well fought, and our thanks; we were sore pressed. You are our honored "
"guests, and I will show you to the best quarters we have myself. Our lord, "
"the runemaster Karrag, will want to have speech with you on the morrow."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:263
msgid ""
"A runemaster? There had been none such since Thursagan's day. And for one to "
"lead a holding was unheard-of; they tended towards the solitary life."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:268
msgid ""
"Aye? Well, you'd know such things better than I, loremaster. Our Karrag "
"toiled for long years to recover the craft lore. He was elevated when our "
"old lord fell in battle against the besieging orcs. Karrag himself was "
"wounded near to death; none thought he would recover. But he leads us today, "
"and his runelore has oft been the only shield between us and the orcs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:273
msgid "He has grasped the Hammer of Thursagan, then?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:278
msgid ""
"Aye. Toils over it in a workshop in the underlevels with his personal "
"followers. He has promised all of us that the Hammer's power will smash and "
"scatter all our enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:283
msgid ""
"That is strange. The Hammer is a tool of crafting and making, not a weapon. "
"What can he mean to do with it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/10_The_Siege_of_Kal_Kartha.cfg:288
msgid ""
"That's for lords and loremasters to worry about, not the likes of me. I must "
"see to my troop's care. Food will be brought to you; rest well, we will "
"speak again."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:3
msgid "The Court of Karrag"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Dwarvish Rune Lord
#. [unit]: type=Lich
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:44
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:243
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:40
msgid "Karrag"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Dwarvish Rune Lord
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:51
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:71
msgid "Kal Karthans"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:163
msgid ""
"(Psst, Angarthing...Karrag and those dwarves on the dais, they're all "
"masked.)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:168
msgid "(I see it. There is something very wrong here.)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:173
msgid "Hail, fellow dwarves. All Kal Kartha thanks you for your timely rescue."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:178
msgid ""
"We are from Knalga; your clans are kin to ours of old. We but did our duty "
"to kin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:183
msgid ""
"All dwarves are kin, and must prevail against orcs and humans and other "
"dirtgrubbers. You can be part of the fist that smites them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:188
msgid "We did not come to smite anyone, but to re-open contact and trade."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:193
msgid ""
"Trade? Your destruction of the besieging orcs was a far nobler act than "
"trade. There can be more such victories. And there will be by the power of "
"our ancient heirloom, the Hammer of Thursagan. "
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:198
msgid "It is remembered in Knalga that Kal Kartha holds the Hammer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:203
msgid ""
"Yes! And the Hammer holds the soul of the dwarves, the true people. "
"Together, we can march to greater victories! Will you of Knalga join me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:208
msgid ""
"On one condition. You must take off that mask and show your true face. I am "
"a witness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:213
msgid ""
"You...do not wish to see what is beneath this mask. I was terribly wounded "
"in an orcish attack. Disfigured."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:218
msgid ""
"But the Law must see. A dwarf must put his name and his face behind his "
"deeds. I am a witness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:223
msgid ""
"Impertinent fool! It is not for you to dictate to a lord in his own holding, "
"much less one who holds the very soul of the dwarves in his hand."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:228
msgid ""
"The Law speaks. Against him with the eyes to see, no deception can hold. I "
"AM A WITNESS!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:261
msgid "No...no...it is horrible! My lord, how did you come to this?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:266
msgid ""
"I lingered for weeks in agony. Only my hatred and the runelore of old "
"sustained me, until I became as I am. I will have revenge; I will destroy "
"the orcs, and the humans, and the elves, and all but the  true people!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Karrag
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:271
msgid ""
"And you have sealed your doom. Hundreds of dirtgrubbers have already died to "
"weave a web of blood around the Hammer and the soul of the dwarves. You and "
"your new friends will be the the last sacrifices I require to bind the "
"entire dwarvish race to my purpose. TAKE THEM!"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:280
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:359
msgid "Defeat Karrag"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:300
msgid ""
"Neither side can recruit or recall. You must win with the troops you have."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:316
msgid ""
"Wait...the lich's apparent death was another illusion. In truth he ran "
"through that doorway behind the throne."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:321
msgid ""
"Then Karrag has fled to the underlevels. None but his masked ones go there "
"any more."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:326
msgid ""
"We must follow. Quickly! It may be his talk of perverting the Hammer was "
"merely mad raving, but we cannot allow the risk that his foul spell might "
"succeed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/11_The_Court_of_Karrag.cfg:342
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:1059
msgid ""
"Without Dulcatulos to explain our actions to the Kal Karthans we'll have to "
"fight them, too. Our mission has failed."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:4
msgid "The Underlevels"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Lich
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:124
msgid "Fleleen"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Lich
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:138
msgid "Lannex"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:293
msgid "This place smells of death."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:298
msgid ""
"It's been...it's been years since I've been down here. Only Karrag and his "
"personal followers used this level. Why did I never wonder about that before?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:303
msgid ""
"Karrag's will, and his dark magic. I think he has been casting glamours on "
"all of you ever since he passed over."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:308
msgid "Where *is* Karrag? We can't have been more than seconds behind him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:313
msgid ""
"This is the Grand Gallery. There are rows of small chambers along its sides; "
"he could have slipped into any of them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:318
msgid ""
"More likely he has cloaked himself, thinking to run ahead to gather his "
"followers. He could be within a spear-cast of us now and we wouldn't know it "
"in this gloom."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dulcatulos
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:327
msgid "Those are war-drums!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aiglondur
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:332
msgid ""
"Aye. Karrag, calling his troops to battle. Only the Dark Gods know what "
"hellspawn the lich will summon. AXES UP!"
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:371
msgid "Death of Dulcatulos"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dranath
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:395
msgid ""
"You cannot pass, fools. The doors I guard are sealed by the power of the "
"Hammer itself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:400
msgid "We'll see about that!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:428
msgid ""
"It sees that guard spoke truth. These doors cannot be forced open by any "
"means we have!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:433
msgid ""
"I sense these bindings to be the work of common sorcery, not the power of "
"the Hammer. Usually to each such locking spell there is some sort of key. If "
"we can but find the key, we will able to open these doors."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:453
msgid "The key has been uttered, these doors should open..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:464
msgid "There we go... faugh, what is that smell!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:490
msgid "I think I hear noises, ahead of us..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:507
msgid "It's locked, but nothing that our hammers can't manage."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:528
msgid "A scroll with some strange writing on it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:533
msgid "I believe that will be the key-spell for that sealed door."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:538
msgid "(reads) Kannin a'kana du'masi a'forigln de'amp."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:543
msgid "Now try the door again, it should open."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:563
#: data/campaigns/The_Hammer_of_Thursagan/scenarios/12_The_Underlevels.cfg:584
msgid "A door. Perhaps Karrag is hiding in here..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
